# File with git-branching commands

## Lists all local branches
```sh
git branch
```

## Creates a new branch
```sh
git branch [branch-name]
```

## Checkout (switch to) a specific branch
```sh
git checkout [branch-name]
```

## Create and checkout a branch
```sh
git checkout -b [branch-name]
```

## Deletes a branch
```sh
git branch -d [branch-name]
```
# Common Git Workflow

```sh
git checkout -b my-new-branch
#... make changes to the files which will require them to be pushed from this branch back to origin
git add .
git commit -m "Description of the changes I made."
git push -u origin my-new-branch
#pushes changes upstream from the newly created branch back to origin
```